From: Olaf Hering <ohering@suse.de>
Subject: kABI: net: ethtool: add ethtool COALESCE_RX_CQE_FRAMES/NSECS
Patch-mainline: Never, kABI workaround
References: bsc#1261256

KABI fixup due to commit dc3d720e12f60 ("net: ethtool: add ethtool COALESCE_RX_CQE_FRAMES/NSECS") 
Prevent loading of this driver built with this change on a kernel without
this change by using a dummy dependency.

increased struct kernel_ethtool_coalesce
Used in struct ethtool_ops via get_coalesce/set_coalesce
 Allocated on stack, drivers will silently receive larger kernel_ethtool_coalesce area.
 Risk if external driver, which was rebuilt with larger kernel_ethtool_coalesce,
 is loaded in an older kernel without this change. Then stack corruption occours.
 But, old kernel lacks ETHTOOL_COALESCE_RX_CQE_FRAMES, so may reject the request.
  Affected drivers: mana. 
 Called from
  __ethnl_set_coalesce
  coalesce_prepare_data
  ethtool_get_coalesce
  ethtool_set_coalesce

Encapsulated in struct coalesce_reply_data as kernel_coalesce  
 Allocated as skb in core kernel via ->reply_size/->reply_data_size
 Larger reply_size/reply_data_size with change
 Populated via -> fill_reply

Acked-by: Olaf Hering <ohering@suse.de>
Acked-by: Michal Koutný <mkoutny@suse.com>
---
 include/linux/ethtool.h |    2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

--- a/include/linux/ethtool.h
+++ b/include/linux/ethtool.h
@@ -228,8 +228,10 @@
 	u32 tx_aggr_max_bytes;
 	u32 tx_aggr_max_frames;
 	u32 tx_aggr_time_usecs;
+#ifndef __GENKSYMS__
 	u32 rx_cqe_frames;
 	u32 rx_cqe_nsecs;
+#endif
 };
 
 /**
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/microsoft/mana/gdma_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/microsoft/mana/gdma_main.c
@@ -2302,11 +2302,13 @@
 	return err;
 }
 
+void suse_kabi_mana_COALESCE_RX_CQE_FRAMES(void);
 static void __exit mana_driver_exit(void)
 {
 	struct mana_dev_recovery *dev;
 	unsigned long flags;
 
+	suse_kabi_mana_COALESCE_RX_CQE_FRAMES();
 	cancel_delayed_work_sync(&mana_dev_recovery_work.work);
 
 	spin_lock_irqsave(&mana_dev_recovery_work.lock, flags);
--- a/drivers/pci/controller/pci-hyperv-intf.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/pci-hyperv-intf.c
@@ -51,6 +51,11 @@
 						  block_invalidate);
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(hyperv_reg_block_invalidate);
+void suse_kabi_mana_COALESCE_RX_CQE_FRAMES(void);
+void suse_kabi_mana_COALESCE_RX_CQE_FRAMES(void)
+{
+}
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(suse_kabi_mana_COALESCE_RX_CQE_FRAMES);
 
 MODULE_DESCRIPTION("Hyper-V PCI Interface");
 MODULE_LICENSE("GPL v2");
